{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:1",
      "text": "For everything there is a season, and a time for every matter under heaven:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:2",
      "text": "a time to be born, and a time to die; a time to plant, and a time to pluck up what is planted;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:3",
      "text": "a time to kill, and a time to heal; a time to break down, and a time to build up;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:4",
      "text": "a time to weep, and a time to laugh; a time to mourn, and a time to dance;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:5",
      "text": "a time to cast away stones, and a time to gather stones together; a time to embrace, and a time to refrain from embracing;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:6",
      "text": "a time to seek, and a time to lose; a time to keep, and a time to cast away;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:7",
      "text": "a time to rend, and a time to sew; a time to keep silence, and a time to speak;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:8",
      "text": "a time to love, and a time to hate; a time for war, and a time for peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:9",
      "text": "What gain has the worker from his toil?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:10",
      "text": "I have seen the business that God has given to the sons of men to be busy with.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:11",
      "text": "He has made everything beautiful in its time; also he has put eternity into man's mind, yet so that he cannot find out what God has done from the beginning to the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:12",
      "text": "I know that there is nothing better for them than to be happy and enjoy themselves as long as they live;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:13",
      "text": "also that it is God's gift to man that every one should eat and drink and take pleasure in all his toil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:14",
      "text": "I know that whatever God does endures for ever; nothing can be added to it, nor anything taken from it; God has made it so, in order that men should fear before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:15",
      "text": "That which is, already has been; that which is to be, already has been; and God seeks what has been driven away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:16",
      "text": "Moreover I saw under the sun that in the place of justice, even there was wickedness, and in the place of righteousness, even there was wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:17",
      "text": "I said in my heart, God will judge the righteous and the wicked, for he has appointed a time for every matter, and for every work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:18",
      "text": "I said in my heart with regard to the sons of men that God is testing them to show them that they are but beasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:19",
      "text": "For the fate of the sons of men and the fate of beasts is the same; as one dies, so dies the other. They all have the same breath, and man has no advantage over the beasts; for all is vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:20",
      "text": "All go to one place; all are from the dust, and all turn to dust again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:21",
      "text": "Who knows whether the spirit of man goes upward and the spirit of the beast goes down to the earth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.3.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 3:22",
      "text": "So I saw that there is nothing better than that a man should enjoy his work, for that is his lot; who can bring him to see what will be after him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
